node.title: Queensland records zero locally acquired COVID cases
node.alt: Queensland Education Minister Grace Grace, with Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk in the background, speaks at a press conference.
node.description: Queensland records zeroÂ locally acquired COVID-19 cases as the state inches close to its 80 per cent double dose milestone.
node.content: ["Queensland has recorded zero locally acquired\u00a0COVID-19 cases.", "Education Minister Grace Grace said the state was inching closer to the 80 per cent double dose milestone and the further easing of restrictions.", "\"This is very good news for Queensland and very good news for schoolies kicking off on the Gold Coast today,\" she said.", "Ms Grace said 72.6 per cent of Queenslanders aged over 16 are now fully vaccinated.", "More than 100 schools around the state are hosting vaccination clinics this weekend\u00a0as part of the second week of the government's\u00a0 'super schools' vaccination blitz.", "Ms Grace said schools would continue to offer vaccines on weekends in areas where vaccination rates were lagging as the state pushes on with its vaccination drive.", "Sports stars, including Brisbane Broncos, Gold Coast Titans, Brisbane Roar and the Queensland Firebirds will be present at schools this weekend as part of the blitz.", "\"We would like to see those vaccination percentages come up and hopefully reach the 90 per cent as soon as possible,\" Ms Grace said.", "\"Do the right thing, take advantage of the super schools blitz weekend.", "\"Every person that gets vaccinated decreases the risk when we open our borders fully of having Delta come in.", "More to come."]
